ldren":[{"type":"text","text":"Discord"}]},{"type":"text","text":" for announcements and communication!"}]},{"type":"h2","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Rules/ToS"}]},{"type":"p","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Objective:"}]},{"type":"ul","children":[{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"The goal of the game is for humans to survive against increasing numbers of creatures of the night while completing designated missions and challenges."}]}]}]},{"type":"p","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Role Assignment:"}]},{"type":"ul","children":[{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Participants will be assigned the role of either a human or a creature of the night at the beginning of the event."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Humans must defend themselves and complete missions to survive."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Creatures of the night must convert humans by tagging them."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Humans must wear their bandana, provided by Tarragon, around their upper arm."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Creatures of the night must wear their bandana as a tail in the back of their pants."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Referees will wear high-vis vests and/or blinking lights."}]}]}]},{"type":"p","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Gameplay:"}]},{"type":"ul","children":[{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Humans will be armed with safe, foam designated weapons."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Creatures of the night will attempt to tag humans to convert them. To accomplish this creatures of the night may run, surround, and otherwise strategize. They may NOT hide in order to ambush, lie about their role, or pretend to be human."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Once tagged, humans must call out “HIT!” and raise their hand. They might become a creature of the night and must join the creature that tagged them. Put the bandana loosely on top of their head. Both the newly converted human and the one who tagged them must convene at the designated location where the kill will be confirmed. If the newly converted human loses their escort AND their bandana is removed from the head by another human, they’re saved from peril and can reenter the game as a human in The Bunker."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Humans can stun creatures of the night by tagging them with foam weapons, removing them temporarily. Creatures of the night must call out “HIT!” and raise their hand. They can respawn in their designated zones."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Creatures of the night can remove another creature from play by removing the tail in the back of their pants. Return their tail so they return to their designated zone to respawn."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Creatures of the night cannot tag in safe zones, designated areas where gameplay is paused. Camping near safe zones is not allowed."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Humans must complete missions and objectives to earn points and advance in the game."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Leaving early is possible by signing out at the bunker. (This counts as a loss for you.)"}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"When a Human is tagged and carrying an objective, weapon, or other; They must bring said item with them and hand it over to the referees at the designated location."}]}]}]},{"type":"p","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Locations"}]},{"type":"ul","children":[{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Safe Zones (You may not play in or near the following areas):"}]}]}]},{"type":"p","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Safety Rules:"}]},{"type":"ul","children":[{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"All participants must adhere to designated safety guidelines and rules provided by event organisers."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"No physical contact (excl. Tagging), tackling, or rough play is allowed."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Participants must respect private property and abide by event boundaries."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Use of any mode of transportation excluding “on foot” is prohibited."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Use of any non-approved weapons or equipment is strictly prohibited. All flashlights or potentially disturbing equipment must be checked by referees."}]}]}]},{"type":"p","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Ending Conditions:"}]},{"type":"ul","children":[{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"The game ends when either all humans have been turned into creatures of the night, all mission objectives have been completed, or at 03:00 (am)."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"If humans successfully complete all missions, they win the game."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"If a team of creatures of the night successfully convert the most humans with none left standing, they win the game."}]}]}]},{"type":"p","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Ticketing:"}]},{"type":"ul","children":[{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Once purchased tickets cannot be returned. If in any case a ticket holder wants to sell their ticket Tarragon must be contacted in order to change the player list accordingly."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Refund requests can be submitted to "},{"type":"a","url":"mailto:Tarragonvzw@gmail.com","title":null,"children":[{"type":"text","text":"Tarragonvzw@gmail.com"}]},{"type":"text","text":" in case of emergency. Tarragon maintains the right to refuse refunds."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Tickets are only valid for this edition of Last Night on Earth."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"By purchasing a ticket you consent to having your picture taken and used by Tarragon for promotional purposes and remain liable for your health and safety during the event."}]}]}]},{"type":"p","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Code of Conduct:"}]},{"type":"ul","children":[{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Respect fellow participants, event staff, and bystanders at all times."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Follow instructions from event organisers and referees promptly."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Cheating, unsportsmanlike behavior, or disruptive conduct will result in immediate disqualification from the game."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Return all handed out equipment to the organisers when signing out or at the end of the event."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Act like your role. Humans will never want to get converted. Creatures of the night shouldn't have mercy."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Have fun, stay active, and embrace the spirit of camaraderie and competition."}]}]}]},{"type":"p","children":[{"type":"text","text":"These rules are designed to ensure a safe, fair, and enjoyable experience for all participants of Last Night on Earth."}]},{"type":"h2","children":[{"type":"text","text":"FAQ"}]},{"type":"p","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Roles"}]},{"type":"ul","children":[{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Humans: Identified by a bandana around the upper arm. Your goal is to survive and complete the missions."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Vampires and Werewolves: Identified by a bandana used as a tail in the back of your pants. Your goal is to convert the most humans with none left standing."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Referees: Identified by high-vis vests and/or blinking lights."}]}]}]},{"type":"p","children":[{"type":"text","text":"What happens if I'm tagged?"}]},{"type":"ul","children":[{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"When humans get tagged by a creature of the night, they call out \"HIT!\" and return with the tagged party to their base of operations. They put their bandana loosely on top of their hand while escorted."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"When creatures of the night get hit by a human's weapon, they call out \"HIT!\", raise their hand and return to their base of operations. Interact with your NPC and you may respawn."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"When a creature of the night removes the tail of another creature of the night, they call out \"TAIL!\" and return the bandana to the other player. That player returns to their base of operations. Interact with your NPC and you may respawn."}]}]}]},{"type":"p","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Where can I find updates?"}]},{"type":"ul","children":[{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"you can find updates in our "},{"type":"a","url":"https://discord.com/invite/95KWPNhKkf","title":null,"children":[{"type":"text","text":"Discord"}]},{"type":"text","text":" (same link as above)."}]}]}]},{"type":"p","children":[{"type":"text","text":"What should I bring?"}]},{"type":"ul","children":[{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Bring your id so we can sign you in."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"A flashlight, water bottle (free water) and comfortable running shoes are recommended."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Feel free to dress up for the occasion."}]}]}]},{"type":"p","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Food and drinks?"}]},{"type":"ul","children":[{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Water is free."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"We sell non-alcoholic beverages."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"There are vending machines in the level with snacks."}]}]}]},{"type":"p","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Weapons & Items"}]},{"type":"ul","children":[{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"All players wear a bandana in various ways."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Humans get a shortened version of a pool noodle. If you break it, you lose it. Return broken weapons to The Bunker. Don't litter."}]}]}]},{"type":"p","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Liability"}]},{"type":"ul","children":[{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"Tarragon VZW is not responsible for any accidents during the event."}]}]},{"type":"li","children":[{"type":"lic","children":[{"type":"text","text":"There is a first aid kit and trained staff available when 